events.description: The Malaysian Palm Oil Board is scheduled to release monthly data on February 10.
Trading of Malaysian palm oil futures on Wednesday.

facts.fact_text: Malaysian palm oil futures held around MYR 4,215 per tonne on Wednesday.

evidences.evidence_text: Malaysian palm oil futures were little changed on Wednesday, holding around MYR 4,215 per tonne after two sessions of losses.

facts.fact_text: India's palm oil imports increased by 51% to reach a four-month high.

evidences.evidence_text: In India, imports surged 51% to a four-month high as palm oil’s steep discount to soyoil spurred refiners’ buying.

facts.fact_text: Indonesia's exports in 2025 reached 23.61 million tonnes, a 9.1% year-on-year increase.

evidences.evidence_text: total 2025 shipments up 9.1% year-on-year at 23.61 million tonnes.

facts.fact_text: Malaysian palm oil exports in January rose between 14.9% and 17.9% month-on-month.

evidences.evidence_text: January shipments estimated to have risen between 14.9%–17.9% month-on-month, according to cargo surveyors.

claims.claim_text: Palm oil prices are expected to stay between MYR 4,000 and MYR 4,300 in February.
claims.author: Malaysian Palm Oil Council

evidences.evidence_text: The Malaysian Palm Oil Council projected prices to hover between MYR 4,000 and MYR 4,300 in February, reflecting balanced market conditions.

claims.claim_text: The upcoming MPOB data is expected to determine the market's next direction.
claims.author: Traders

evidences.evidence_text: Traders remained cautious ahead of the Malaysian Palm Oil Board’s monthly data, due February 10, which is expected to set a fresh direction.

evidence.evidence_text: Price action stayed muted as a stronger ringgit and firmer Chicago soyoil offset support from gains in Dalian vegetable oils.
